play lunch
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a snack (apple etc) eaten during the morning play period or playtime.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: "Consumed at morning play time, in my school days & in my children's in the 50's and 60's - fruit, a "cookie" (the word came in the latter period) or a sandwich." (Miss Clouston). ca1930 P.B. Trapp (10.10.63) ca1950 at least P. Ranby (Auckland) p.c.
